[1]
Date: Wed, 01 Feb 2006 20:05:40 -0600
From: M. Randolph Kruger <mail25368@bellsouth.net>

We are told here that there is evidence that skunks and raccoons are
carrying it [rabies]. There are signs posted in the grocery stores
around the Tennessee/Alabama/Mississippi border region (Pickwick
Lake/Tombigbee waterway area) giving the symptoms for rabies. Signs
say that that if anyone should see an animal displaying it that they
should monitor them while someone calls animal control. If they are
unable to get them and the animal is getting away then they are to
shoot and kill it if able.
No one knows why it keeps turning up with all of the vaccinations
that have taken place. Is there such a thing as an asymptomatic
rabies carrier other than bats?
--
Randy Kruger
Collierville TN
<mail25368@bellsouth.net>
